 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Jupiter and Fortune. A Fable.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, from out the Skies,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beheld a thousand Temples rise;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Goddess  all invok'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">an Altar seldom smoak'd:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The God resolv'd to make Inspection,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What had occasion'd this Defection;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And bid the Goddess tell the Arts,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">By which she won deluded Hearts.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Arts! (says she) Great , you know,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That I do ev'ry Thing below:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I make my Vot'ries dine on Plate;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I give the gilded Coach of State;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bestow the glitt'ring Gems, that deck</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The fair  lovely Neck;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I make  Nature's Boast,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And raise  to a Toast;</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis I, who give the Stupid, Taste,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(Or make the Poets lie, at least);</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My fav'rite Sons, whene'er they please,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can Palaces in Desarts raise,</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Cut out Canals, make Fountains play,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And make the dreary Waste look gay;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ev'n Vice seems Virtue by my Smiles;</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I gild the Villain's gloomy Wiles,</l>
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nay, almost raise him to a God,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">While crowded Levees wait his Nod.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">â€” the Thunderer reply'd;</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But say, whom have you satisfy'd?</l>
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">These boasted Gifts are thine, I own;</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But know, Content is mine alone.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
